Sentencas: The behavior of silver as the solid oxide fuel cell SOFC cathode material was investigated.
Titulo: Changes in the morphology and the composition of the Ag|Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 interface caused by polarization

Sentencas: Ag vertical bar Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 half cells were cathodically polarized at the temperatures between 300 and 700 degrees C at the potential of -0.5 V. Changes in the morphology and electronic states of the electrolyte surface on the cathodic side were examined by the Scanning Electron Microscopy and Energy Dispersive X-ray Spectroscopy.
Titulo: Changes in the morphology and the composition of the Ag|Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 interface caused by polarization

Sentencas: Silver deposits arose around the point where electrodes contact the electrolyte.
Titulo: Changes in the morphology and the composition of the Ag|Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 interface caused by polarization

Sentencas: The negative polarization did not change electronic states of cerium and gadolinium in the electrolyte surface region.
Titulo: Changes in the morphology and the composition of the Ag|Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 interface caused by polarization

Sentencas: The mechanism of the silver migration is proposed.
